eg.ui

Class ConsolePanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • eg.ui.ConsolePanel

  • public class ConsolePanel
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines the panel which contains a text area for messages and for reading in text and also a toolbar.

    Initially, the text area is not editable and not focusable and also buttons in the toolbar are disabled.

      • setActive

        public void setActive(boolean isActive)
        Sets the active or the inactive state. Active means that text area is editable and focusable and also that this stop button is enabled.
        Parameters:
        isActive - true for the active, false for the inactive sate

      • isActive

        public boolean isActive()
        Returns if the active state is set.

        The active state should indicate that this text area is used by a started process.

        Returns:
        the boolean value, true if the active state is set
